early Latin, words of four sylla- bles,the first three of which were all short, were regularly accented on the first; so pilosopos (57), mu'lieres (117), etc. In Cicero's day contracted genitives like benefici and consili were accented on the penult, but early Latin verse indicates that at that time they followed the same accentual laws as other words.
